# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# Do NOT commit .env.local (it's gitignored). Add the same vars in
# Vercel -> Project -> Settings -> Environment Variables for production.

# --- Spotify "now playing" ---------------------------------------------------
# 1. https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard -> Create app.
#    Redirect URI: http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/spotify/callback
# 2. Copy Client ID + Client Secret below.
# 3. Get the refresh token: set the two above, restart dev, visit
#    http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/spotify/login and approve — it prints the token.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# --- Steam "recently played" -------------------------------------------------
# 1. Free Web API key: https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey
# 2. Your 64-bit SteamID (steamid64) — e.g. paste your profile URL into
#    https://steamid.io and copy the "steamID64" number.
# 3. Steam profile + "game details" privacy must be set to Public.
STEAM_API_KEY=
STEAM_ID=

# --- TMDB (Shows / Movies posters) -------------------------------------------
# Free API key: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api  (sign up -> API ->
# create -> use the "API Key (v3 auth)" value).
TMDB_API_KEY=

# --- GitHub (auto-pulled Projects) -------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL. Without it, the public GitHub API allows 60 requests/hour, which is
# usually fine. A read-only token raises that to 5000/hr.
# Create at https://github.com/settings/tokens (classic, NO scopes needed for
# public repos) or a fine-grained token with read-only public access.

